##Japanese schools are closed and the government is prepared to pay workers to stay at home with their children

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

The paper's reporter, Nan Boyi, an intern, Liu Yukun

On March 9th the Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare issued detailed rules on wage subsidies, among other things, in response to the temporary suspension of classes due to the spread of the new crown disease.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A closed public primary school in Japan. Xinhua map

据《日本经济新闻》报道，新补助金制度的主要对象是为了照顾孩子而不能上班的职工。除了日本首相安倍晋三要求停课的中小学、幼儿园以及托儿所等场所的工作人员外，没有得到官方认可的保育机构、托儿所以及“保育妈妈”（保育ママ，针对3岁以下儿童的非正式保育员）也在受助范围内。

During the period from February 27 to March 31, recipients will receive a maximum of 8,330 yen (about 555 yuan) per day, the form in which they are employed by the company and the size of the company will not affect the amount of the grant.

According to the Asahi Shimbun, the grant is not limited to the child's guardian, but can also be paid if the child's grandparents take time off from work to care for the child.

In addition to the case of a full day of rest for employees, half a day of leave is also available for the corresponding period of benefits.

Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe announced on February 27th that all primary, middle and high schools across the country would be suspended from March 2nd because of the spread of the infection. "Every region is working to prevent the virus from spreading among children, and this is a very important period in one or two weeks, " Anbe said. As of Friday morning local time, the suspension rate of primary and secondary schools across Japan had reached 99 percent, Minister of Education, Culture, Sports, Science and Technology of Japan Ogiu told the Senate Budget Committee on the temporary suspension of classes due to the new pneumonia outbreak.

This issue is edited by Chang Chen
